* Task 5 fixture: static CALLNAT binding in flat namespace (FR-10, M-3, NFR-7)
* Demonstrates:
* - CALLNAT 'MYSUB' (literal static target, matches one definition) → should resolve to MYSUB.NSN
* - CALLNAT 'NOSUCH' (literal static target, no matching object) → should resolve as Unresolved(ReasonNoTarget)
*
* This fixture covers the flat-namespace, exactly-one-match case with no library map.
* The two calls prove that resolution binds literal names correctly and distinguishes
* "found the target" from "target not found" without inventing a definition.

DEFINE DATA
LOCAL
  1 RESULT (A10)
END DEFINE

* Static call to resolvable external subprogram
CALLNAT 'MYSUB'

* Static call with no matching definition (literal target name not found)
CALLNAT 'NOSUCH'

* Use the result variable to complete the structure
MOVE 'OK' TO RESULT

END
